    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "DEFINITION: An ordered set of geographic points that defines a path from a starting point to an ending point."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "NOTE: A geographic route could describe a bus route by identifying the points where the bus stops. A geographic route could describe the boundary of a polygonal geographic region (it does not have to be a traveled route)."
